# data-models-relationships

## Core Data Models

### Youth Profile Schema
- Hierarchical behavioral rating system across 4 domains:
  - Peer interaction
  - Adult interaction 
  - Investment level
  - Authority handling
- Treatment progression tracking with 10 levels + orientation
- Medical profile with structured medication/allergy tracking
- Professional contact relationship mapping
- Behavioral incident classification system

### Assessment Models
- HYRNA risk assessment with 8 weighted domains
- Real Colors personality matrix (Heart, Anchor, Mind, Spark)
- Individual Service Plan (ISP) framework
- Treatment goal hierarchy with categorized objectives

### Progress Tracking Schema
- Point-based privilege system
- Academic performance metrics
- Behavioral incident severity classification
- Color assessment status tracking
- Professional relationship management

## Key Relationships

### Youth to Assessments
- One-to-many relationship between youth and behavioral assessments
- Assessments drive treatment level assignments
- Risk scores map to program level recommendations
- Personality assessments influence staff interaction guidelines

### Youth to Progress Data
- Daily behavioral ratings link to monthly averages
- Point totals determine level progression
- Incident records associate with behavioral trends
- Academic scores integrate with behavioral assessments

### Professional Relationships
- Role-based associations (legal, medical, educational)
- Unique professional type constraints
- Contact management hierarchies
- Treatment team assignments

